en_66359_0	The National Transport Commission reiterated that the government is the sole authority to make bus fare revisions.
en_66359_1	NTC Chairman Roshan Gunawardana said that the Cabinet subcommittee which was appointed to look into the bus fare revision will take a final decision in the future.
en_66359_2	Although the Lanka Private Bus Owners Association insisted a bus fare hike with effect from 01 st of September, it was not realized.
en_66359_3	Speaking to our news team the President of the Lanka Private Bus Owners Association Gemunu Wijerathna said that the government appointed a Cabinet subcommittee and arbitrarily took over powers vested with Bus Unions to make fare revisions.
en_66359_4	He also said that his Association expects to take legal action against this move by the government.
